-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Apple, Netscout Systems  
-- 
-- Fri Jul 11, 2014 03:05AM EDT
-- None



July 11 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including Apple and LAM Research, on Friday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Apple <AAPL.O>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to $112 from $102 * LAM Research <LRCX.O>: Jefferies raises target price to $84   Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Friday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Alaska Air Group <ALK.N>: Deutsche adjusts target to $42.50 from $85 to reflect stocksplit * API Technologies <ATNY.O>: B. Riley cuts target price to $3.75; buy rating * Apple <AAPL.O>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to $112 from $102; rating buy  * CHC Group <HELI.N>: UBS cuts target price to $11 from $12; rating buy * GAP <GPS.N>: Sterne Agee cuts target price to $46 from $47; rating buy * KLA-Tencor <KLAC.O>: Jefferies raises target price to $75; rating hold  * LAM Research <LRCX.O>: Jefferies raises target price to $84; rating buy  * Netscout Systems <NTCT.O>: B. Riley raises price target to $54 from $45; buy rating * Regency Centers <REG.N>: Deutsche Bank raises target price to $55 from $51; rating hold